---
// biome-ignore lint/correctness/noUnusedImports: used in Astro template
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Learn about clip — the open-source tool that turns API schemas into CLI tools.">
  <div class="about">
    <div class="about-inner">
      <h1>About clip</h1>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>What is clip?</h2>
        <p>
          clip is an open-source tool that generates fully working CLI tools from
          a YAML schema. Instead of manually writing argument parsers, HTTP
          clients, and authentication logic, you define your API once and let
          clip handle the rest.
        </p>
        <p>
          The goal is simple: if you have an API, you should be able to interact
          with it from the command line without writing a single line of CLI
          code.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Why clip?</h2>
        <p>
          Most APIs ship without a CLI. The ones that do have CLIs require
          significant engineering effort to build and maintain. clip eliminates
          that work by generating the entire CLI from a declarative schema.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Schema-first</strong> — One YAML file drives everything</li>
          <li><strong>Zero boilerplate</strong> — No manual argument parsing or HTTP plumbing</li>
          <li><strong>Auto-tested</strong> — Generated tests validate API response shapes</li>
          <li><strong>Secure by default</strong> — Credentials stored with restricted permissions</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Technology</h2>
        <p>clip is built with modern tools for speed and simplicity:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bun</strong> — JavaScript runtime and package manager</li>
          <li><strong>TypeScript</strong> — Strict types throughout</li>
          <li><strong>Commander.js</strong> — Argument parsing in generated CLIs</li>
          <li><strong>Astro</strong> — This documentation site</li>
          <li><strong>Biome</strong> — Linting and formatting</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Open Source</h2>
        <p>
          clip is open source and available on
          <a
            href="https://github.com/user/clip"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a
          >. Contributions, issues, and feedback are welcome.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding: var(--space-xl) 0 calc(var(--space-xl) * 2);
  }

  .about-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-lg);
  }

  .about-inner h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .about-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .about-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .about-section p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .about-section ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .about-section li {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-inner {
      padding: 0 var(--space-md);
    }
  }
</style>
